<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4685039>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4.Uroptychus insignis (Henderson, 1885).(A) female pcl 4.4 mm, Kerguelen Islands (MNHN IU-2010-5432).(B–E) paralectotype, male pcl 4.5 mm (BMNH 1902.10.2.9–14). (F) female pcl 7.2 mm, Kerguelen Islands (AM P97999). (G) paralectotype, male pcl 10.7 mm, (BMNH 1902.10.2.9–14). (H–I) male pcl 11.5 mm, Crozet Islands (MNHN IU-2010-5427). (J–L) female pcl 2.9 mm, Kerguelen Islands (MNHN IU-2010-5432). (A, B, G, H) carapace and proximal articles of P1; (C–E) right P2–4; (F) carapace; (I) right P1; (J–L) left pereopods 2–4; Scale: A–E = 2.5 mm; F–I = 5.0 mm; J–L = 1.0 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4685039/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4685037>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 3.Uroptychus insignis (Henderson, 1885), lectotype, ov.female, pcl 10.6 mm, (BMNH 1902.10.2.9–14).(A) carapace and anterior part of abdomen, proximal part of left cheliped, dorsal. (B) carapace and abdomen, right lateral. (C) sternal plastron. (D) telson. (E) left antenna, ventral. F, left maxilliped 3, ventral. (G) same, setae omitted, lateral. (H) left P1, setae omitted. (I) left P1 fingers, ventral view. (J) left P1 ischium and merus, ventral. (K) same, proximal part, lateral. (L–N) right P2–4. (O–Q) same, distal articles. Scales: A, B, H–N = 5 mm; C = 2.0 mm; D–G, O–Q = 2.5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4685037/files/figure.png" .

